text: 220px Māris Ārbergs (born 1962) is a Latvian politician. He was a Deputy of the Saeima from 2006 to 2010, as a member of the People's Party. ==References== Category:1962 births Category:Living people Category:People's Party (Latvia) politicians Category:Deputies of the 9th Saeima
title: Māris Ārbergs
